# INTERPRETATION
# 1280x960 P010_VENUS = EXACTLY 0x384000 (byteStride 2560 * 1.5*960 = 2560*1440). IDENTICAL to the LOS
#   tombstone_36 buffer (00000074'14df4000-00000074'15177fff = 0x384000). So dmabuf len is NOT the divergence.
# (Earlier run mis-labeled the 960x1280 buffer "PADDED" using a hardcoded 0x384000; with the correct
#  stride-1024 math 0x3c0000 IS the exact contiguous size — both OOS buffers are exact, zero tail padding.)
# The page IMMEDIATELY AFTER the 1280x960 buffer end (0x7c4f400000) is a MAPPED rw- /dmabuf:AHardwareBuffer
# NEIGHBOR on OOS — so BasicTone's tail fencepost over-read reads a garbage value but does NOT fault.
# On LOS the same offset is a PROT_NONE guard page -> SIGSEGV. Same buffer size, different heap placement.
